		<div class="content container_12">

			<section clas="welcome">

				<div class="welcome-video grid_6">
					<div class="cms_region" id="home_welcome_video">Video</div>
				</div>
				<div class="welcome-message grid_6">
					<div class="cms_region" id="home_welcome_message">
						<h2>Content management should be <span>easy</span></h2>
						<p>Stackbox CMS is an ambitious new open source content management system aimed to end the "backend" editing paradigm for good. All content editing is done directly in-place and on-page through drag-and-drop, JavaScript and AJAX methods.</p>
						<p>
							<a class="button button-download" href="/"><i></i>Download Stackbox</a>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

			</section>
			<section class="features">		
					
					<div class="feature-edit grid_4">
						<div class="cms_region" id="feature_1">
							<h3 class="title">Edit right on the page</h3>
							<p>Content Management Systems shouldn't have big bloated admin areas to learn. Just add tags to your template and Stackbox lets you edit directly on the page. Integrating with your current HTML couldn't be easier.</p>
							<p><a href="interior.html">Find out more about templates</a>.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="feature-free grid_4">
						<div class="cms_region" id="feature_2">
							<h3 class="title">Did we mention it's free?</h3>
							<p>With Stackbox your site lives on your server, so you don't have to worry about paying expensive hosting fees just to get a content management system. We built Stackbox using PHP5 and MySQL to be compatible with almost all hosting environments.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="feature-open grid_4">
						<div class="cms_region" id="feature_3">
							<h3 class="title">White Label &amp; Open Source</h3>
							<p>Stackbox is an open-source project, so you are free to make it your own. Don't see a feature you want? Build it! Then share back with the community, or build a module for the Stackbox Marketplace (coming soon).</p>
						</div>
					</div>

			</section>

		</div>
